WEBVTT

00:01.540 --> 00:06.290
♪♪

00:06.290 --> 00:08.290
Dre: The United States holds
almost a quarter

00:08.290 --> 00:10.080
of the world's prisoners.

00:10.080 --> 00:11.540
[ Cell door clangs ]

00:11.540 --> 00:13.540
♪ I'm steady
tryin' to find a motive ♪

00:13.540 --> 00:14.500
♪ Motive ♪

00:14.500 --> 00:16.420
♪ Why I do what I do ♪

00:16.420 --> 00:19.500
2.2 million Americans
are behind bars,

00:19.500 --> 00:23.830
a 500% increase
over the past 40 years.

00:23.830 --> 00:27.380
Black people make up 13%
of the American population

00:27.380 --> 00:30.580
but 35%
of the prisons' population.

00:30.580 --> 00:33.290
65 million Americans
have a criminal record.

00:33.290 --> 00:37.000
1 in 28 American children
have a parent behind bars.

00:37.000 --> 00:40.040
We get our incarceration on!
[ Cell door clangs ]

00:40.040 --> 00:40.920
♪ If I get locked up ♪

00:40.920 --> 00:43.710
♪ They won't let me out ♪

00:43.710 --> 00:46.040
♪ They won't let me out ♪

00:46.040 --> 00:48.460
Prisons have become
uninhabitable.

00:48.460 --> 00:51.750
It's easy for people
to start feeling like numbers.

00:51.750 --> 00:54.460
And one of those numbers
happens to be my godbrother.

00:54.460 --> 00:56.210
[ Telephone rings, beeps ]

00:56.210 --> 00:58.080
Female voice: You have
a collect call from...

00:58.080 --> 00:59.540
Man: I need money.

00:59.540 --> 01:01.210
Dre:
And now you've met Omar.

01:06.920 --> 01:08.420
Female voice:
To accept this call,

01:08.420 --> 01:10.210
say or dial "five" now.

01:10.210 --> 01:12.250
We're sorry. The number
that you have reached

01:12.250 --> 01:14.670
has been disconnected
or is no longer in service.

01:14.670 --> 01:15.500
[ Phone beeps, receiver clicks ]

01:15.500 --> 01:17.250
Dre, was that Omar?
Yep.

01:17.250 --> 01:18.750
Why didn't you
accept his call?

01:18.750 --> 01:20.960
Because this is the third time
he's called this week,

01:20.960 --> 01:23.000
and he's constantly
asking me,

01:23.000 --> 01:24.330
"Who was at the club
last night?"

01:24.330 --> 01:25.960
I don't have the heart
to tell him

01:25.960 --> 01:27.830
that the club
is a Gymboree now.

01:27.830 --> 01:29.080
Dre, my goodness.

01:29.080 --> 01:31.000
You sound so cold.
Mnh-mnh.

01:31.000 --> 01:32.460
He just wants
human contact.

01:32.460 --> 01:33.830
You can't just talk to him
for a little bit?

01:33.830 --> 01:35.170
You talk to him plenty.

01:35.170 --> 01:36.120
Beyoncé's looking

01:36.120 --> 01:37.170
at another Beyoncé,

01:37.170 --> 01:38.080
and she's underwater

01:38.080 --> 01:39.170
for some reason.

01:39.170 --> 01:39.920
Now she's walking

01:39.920 --> 01:41.330
down the courtroom steps.

01:41.330 --> 01:43.880
And there's water gushing out.

01:43.880 --> 01:45.670
She's in a yellow dress,

01:45.670 --> 01:46.790
and she's mad.

01:46.790 --> 01:48.540
[ Gasps ] She is so mad.

01:48.540 --> 01:52.830
It's a Santa Maria Pinot Grigio,
single vineyard.

01:52.830 --> 01:54.120
Very earthy notes.

01:54.120 --> 01:56.750
What would I be
if I wasn't a doctor?

01:56.750 --> 01:58.170
I don't know.

01:58.170 --> 01:59.580
A dancer?

01:59.580 --> 02:01.710
[ Laughing ]

02:01.710 --> 02:02.830
No.

02:02.830 --> 02:05.290
Not that kind of dancer.

02:05.290 --> 02:07.540
Omar, you are so silly.

02:07.540 --> 02:10.580
You two have a very
inappropriate relationship.

02:10.580 --> 02:11.460
I don't send him

02:11.460 --> 02:12.750
pictures anymore.

02:12.750 --> 02:13.920
[ Chuckles ] He traded those in

02:13.920 --> 02:15.040
for a cell with a window.

02:15.040 --> 02:17.040
You think I'm worth that?
No.

02:17.040 --> 02:18.750
I am just trying

02:18.750 --> 02:20.670
to make prison easier
for him.

02:20.670 --> 02:22.620
Prison shouldn't be easy!

02:22.620 --> 02:24.290
When I was on the inside,

02:24.290 --> 02:25.960
I had to do my own things

02:25.960 --> 02:27.250
to get extra cornbread.

02:27.250 --> 02:28.620
Here we go.

02:28.620 --> 02:30.750
You know how they say
snitches get stitches?

02:30.750 --> 02:31.790
-Mm-hmm.
-Oh, God.

02:31.790 --> 02:32.580
Well, when you're locked up,

02:32.580 --> 02:34.460
snitches also

02:34.460 --> 02:36.080
[chuckles] get cornbread.

02:36.080 --> 02:37.420
Hey.

02:37.420 --> 02:38.580
-Dre.
-Hmm?

02:38.580 --> 02:41.250
I just don't want him
to feel so alone.

02:41.250 --> 02:43.460
I love that you want
to help everyone,

02:43.460 --> 02:45.750
but there's only so much
that you can do.

02:45.750 --> 02:46.750
I guess so.

02:46.750 --> 02:48.420
He's behind bars.
I know that.

02:48.420 --> 02:50.580
So you have to keep
a healthy distance.

02:50.580 --> 02:52.170
But his birthday's coming up.

02:52.170 --> 02:53.420
We can still get him a cake,
right?

02:53.420 --> 02:55.540
You don't have birthdays
in jail.

02:55.540 --> 02:56.880
It's true.

02:56.880 --> 02:58.960
Technically,
I never turned 39.

02:58.960 --> 03:00.040
Oh, my God.

03:00.040 --> 03:01.710
Or stab a bitch named Sheila

03:01.710 --> 03:03.290
in the belly.

03:03.290 --> 03:04.670
[ Chuckles ] I got her!

03:04.670 --> 03:06.420
[ Sighs ]

03:06.420 --> 03:08.460
That was an awful casual mention

03:08.460 --> 03:09.920
of you going to jail

03:09.920 --> 03:11.460
and stabbing Sheila, Grandma.

03:11.460 --> 03:12.790
Huh?

03:12.790 --> 03:15.080
Oh, no, baby.

03:15.080 --> 03:16.920
Grandma never
went to jail.

03:16.920 --> 03:18.500
I think you might be lying,

03:18.500 --> 03:19.710
because I just heard you say

03:19.710 --> 03:21.040
you went to jail.

03:21.040 --> 03:22.330
[ Chuckles ]

03:22.330 --> 03:24.000
You heard that?

03:24.000 --> 03:25.420
Come on, Grandma.

03:25.420 --> 03:26.830
I can handle the truth.

03:26.830 --> 03:28.710
I shave twice a month now.

03:28.710 --> 03:30.420
All right. Fine.

03:30.420 --> 03:31.580
Many years ago,

03:31.580 --> 03:32.790
I blew up Earl's boat.

03:32.790 --> 03:33.960
Bad.

03:33.960 --> 03:34.960
[ Explosion ]

03:34.960 --> 03:40.960
[ Laughing ]

03:40.960 --> 03:43.670
I was charged
with some aquatic crime,

03:43.670 --> 03:46.710
got thrown
in some local maritime jail,

03:46.710 --> 03:48.120
and shared a cell

03:48.120 --> 03:52.500
with a sicko who got off
on torturing dolphins.

03:52.500 --> 03:55.540
Can you imagine?
The angels of the sea!

03:55.540 --> 03:56.790
Wow.

03:56.790 --> 03:58.290
I can't believe that.
Yeah.

03:58.290 --> 04:00.500
Thanks for sharing
your secret with me.

04:00.500 --> 04:01.540
Ohh.

04:01.540 --> 04:02.920
[ Chuckles ]

04:02.920 --> 04:05.750
An experience like that
must have changed you.

04:05.750 --> 04:07.170
Mm, no.

04:07.170 --> 04:09.710
Not learning lessons
is kind of my thing.

04:09.710 --> 04:12.710
♪♪

04:12.710 --> 04:13.500
Okay, ready?

04:13.500 --> 04:15.620
Front, front,
back, back.

04:15.620 --> 04:18.080
Pat your weave,
pat your weave.

04:18.080 --> 04:19.540
I'm not
patting my weave.

04:19.540 --> 04:21.580
So, you don't care
if we have a hot handshake?

04:21.580 --> 04:23.920
I guess you're happy
with being replaced, then?

04:23.920 --> 04:27.330
Aw, the twins
are here!

04:27.330 --> 04:28.120
Yep.

04:28.120 --> 04:29.790
[ Laughs ]

04:29.790 --> 04:31.170
Aw!

04:31.170 --> 04:32.580
I'm Dylan.

04:32.580 --> 04:35.080
Or am I Dylan?

04:35.080 --> 04:37.710
Ohh!
It's just adorable!

04:37.710 --> 04:39.040
Girls: Yeah!

04:39.040 --> 04:40.460
Or do you want to stay
two low-rent suckers

04:40.460 --> 04:41.540
with the same birthday?

04:41.540 --> 04:43.750
[ Sighs ] Fine.
I'll pat the weave.

04:43.750 --> 04:46.080
But call me "low-rent" again,
and we're done.

04:46.080 --> 04:47.040
[ Scoffs ]

04:47.040 --> 04:48.170
Ready?

04:48.170 --> 04:50.250
Front, front,
back, back.

04:50.250 --> 04:51.540
Pat your weave,
pat your...

04:51.540 --> 04:54.540
So, am I the bad guy
for keeping my distance

04:54.540 --> 04:57.170
when Bow's the one
who's been leading Omar on

04:57.170 --> 04:59.120
by talking to him
almost every day

04:59.120 --> 05:00.880
and sending pictures
of herself to him?

05:00.880 --> 05:02.500
Probably
in a bathing suit.

05:02.500 --> 05:04.380
Mm.
Unacceptable.

05:04.380 --> 05:06.580
[ Whispering ] I should
probably see those.

05:06.580 --> 05:08.120
Ch--

05:08.120 --> 05:10.170
You know, just to make sure
they unacceptable.

05:10.170 --> 05:12.960
Dre, I don't like weighing in
on your personal business,

05:12.960 --> 05:14.120
but you're right.

05:14.120 --> 05:16.790
You shouldn't be associating
with prisoners.

05:16.790 --> 05:18.620
They're animals.
Whoa, whoa.

05:18.620 --> 05:19.880
I never said
they were animals.

05:19.880 --> 05:21.500
No, no, no, no, no.

05:21.500 --> 05:24.380
They're just people
who live in cages,

05:24.380 --> 05:26.330
and regular people
come and visit them

05:26.330 --> 05:28.120
and watch them
through glass.

05:28.120 --> 05:29.710
Okay,
I'm a little confused.

05:29.710 --> 05:31.920
So, is Darrington
over there...
Mm-hmm.

05:31.920 --> 05:33.460
...is he an animal?

05:33.460 --> 05:35.790
Because didn't you hire him
right from prison?

05:35.790 --> 05:39.210
Darrington has paid
his debt to society.

05:39.210 --> 05:42.000
He served six
long months inside.

05:42.000 --> 05:43.620
Mm-hmm.
Okay, you're talking
white-collar,

05:43.620 --> 05:45.790
Club Fed,
Martha Stewart time.

05:45.790 --> 05:48.000
I'm talking real time.

05:48.000 --> 05:50.170
What, Darrington's time
wasn't real?

05:50.170 --> 05:52.500
Okay, he had to play
doubles tennis,

05:52.500 --> 05:54.710
medium-rare was
more like medium,

05:54.710 --> 05:58.500
and the only premium
movie channel he had
in there was Epix.

05:58.500 --> 06:00.580
So, what did
Darrington do?

06:00.580 --> 06:03.080
He bankrupted Burma
and was caught

06:03.080 --> 06:04.330
with a gentleman's
amount of cocaine.

06:04.330 --> 06:07.500
-Oh, I loved cocaine!
-Hmm.

06:07.500 --> 06:08.710
Yeah,
without cocaine,

06:08.710 --> 06:11.420
I wouldn't need these glasses
or my pacemaker.

06:11.420 --> 06:12.580
Curtis: That's --
That's messed up.

06:12.580 --> 06:15.210
See, my cousin got caught with
a gentleman's amount of crack.

06:15.210 --> 06:16.620
Same thing as coke.

06:16.620 --> 06:18.670
And he got five years.

06:18.670 --> 06:20.420
You know how much coke he would
have had to have had on him

06:20.420 --> 06:22.500
to get the same sentence?

06:22.500 --> 06:23.580
500 grams.

06:23.580 --> 06:25.500
That's because
coke is a white drug.

06:25.500 --> 06:26.830
It's a magical powder

06:26.830 --> 06:29.210
that you snort through
a rolled-up hundo in Aspen

06:29.210 --> 06:30.620
with boobies in your face.

06:30.620 --> 06:33.790
Now, crack is considered
a black drug.

06:33.790 --> 06:34.790
It's dirty.

06:34.790 --> 06:36.170
You smoke it
through a rusty pipe,

06:36.170 --> 06:38.420
and there are no big old boobies
anywhere to be found.

06:38.420 --> 06:40.620
See, the system is built
to hem a brother up,

06:40.620 --> 06:43.170
while you white folks
just get a slap on the wrist.

06:43.170 --> 06:45.420
A slap on the wrist?

06:45.420 --> 06:48.540
Darrington has to pick up
trash on beaches.

06:48.540 --> 06:51.000
That's the difference
between white-collar

06:51.000 --> 06:53.040
and black-collar crimes.

06:53.040 --> 06:56.170
We're treated unfairly
while we're free,

06:56.170 --> 06:58.920
and treated even worse
while we're behind bars.
Mm-hmm.

06:58.920 --> 07:02.380
So, why are you
so mad at your wife

07:02.380 --> 07:04.330
for trying to improve the life
for your jail friend?

07:04.330 --> 07:05.830
Stevens: Look at that.

07:05.830 --> 07:08.750
We just had an entire discussion
about black people

07:08.750 --> 07:10.790
with no mention
of slavery.
Okay.

07:10.790 --> 07:12.380
This calls
for a celebration.

07:12.380 --> 07:13.750
Darrington!

07:13.750 --> 07:15.250
You still
on the wagon?

07:15.250 --> 07:17.460
If he isn't, we'll know.
He's an animal.

07:17.460 --> 07:20.620
Those coked-up monsters at work
made me realize

07:20.620 --> 07:22.960
that I needed to start
taking Omar's calls.

07:22.960 --> 07:25.750
Hell, maybe I'd even let Bow
send him a few more pictures.

07:25.750 --> 07:26.960
-Dre.
-Huh?

07:26.960 --> 07:28.250
Dre, I just got
the best news.

07:28.250 --> 07:29.330
Omar just called.

07:29.330 --> 07:31.330
The Innocence Project
stepped in!

07:31.330 --> 07:32.540
He is innocent!

07:32.540 --> 07:33.830
Wait, what?!

07:33.830 --> 07:35.000
He's getting out!

07:35.000 --> 07:36.210
-Out?
-Yes!

07:36.210 --> 07:37.330
From jail?
Yes!

07:37.330 --> 07:38.670
Omar?!
Yes, Dre!

07:38.670 --> 07:39.750
They are
letting him out,

07:39.750 --> 07:41.920
and he's -- he's gonna
get his life back.

07:41.920 --> 07:43.540
Look at God.

07:43.540 --> 07:45.420
All right, uh, so I suppose
I should probably,

07:45.420 --> 07:47.790
you know, pick him up
so he can crash here.

07:47.790 --> 07:48.920
Here?
Yes!

07:48.920 --> 07:50.120
Omar?
Yes!

07:50.120 --> 07:51.000
From jail?

07:51.000 --> 07:51.920
Bow, you were the one

07:51.920 --> 07:53.040
that was talking to him.

07:53.040 --> 07:54.380
Where else would he go
when he got out?

07:54.380 --> 07:55.880
Who got out?
Omar.

07:55.880 --> 07:57.250
From jail?
Yes!

07:57.250 --> 07:59.040
Look at God!
Uh-huh.

07:59.040 --> 08:00.330
♪♪

08:04.000 --> 08:05.420
♪♪

08:05.420 --> 08:06.790
So, Omar's free?

08:06.790 --> 08:08.170
-Yeah.
-Ooh.

08:08.170 --> 08:11.210
A man who's been locked up
for 10 long years

08:11.210 --> 08:12.710
without the touch
of a woman

08:12.710 --> 08:14.080
is coming
to this house.

08:14.080 --> 08:16.120
Well,
it's such bad timing,

08:16.120 --> 08:19.960
because I've lost
the belts to all my robes.

08:19.960 --> 08:21.330
Yes.

08:21.330 --> 08:22.920
Ew!

08:22.920 --> 08:25.580
Dre, why does
he have to come here?

08:25.580 --> 08:26.920
You were the one
that said

08:26.920 --> 08:28.920
we had to keep a healthy
distance from people in prison.

08:28.920 --> 08:30.580
Yeah,
but he's getting out

08:30.580 --> 08:32.830
into a world
that doesn't care for him.

08:32.830 --> 08:34.540
Bow, we need
to help him.

08:34.540 --> 08:37.290
We can get him a really nice
room at AmeriSuites.

08:37.290 --> 08:39.540
You once said the AmeriSuites
was prison.

08:39.540 --> 08:41.500
You can hear the ice machines
all night long.

08:41.500 --> 08:43.750
Unbelievable!
What?

08:43.750 --> 08:45.120
So, when he was
in a cage,

08:45.120 --> 08:47.830
you were just fine sending him
food and pictures.

08:47.830 --> 08:50.540
And...money.

08:50.540 --> 08:51.460
Money?

08:51.460 --> 08:53.330
Just like
$300 a month.

08:53.330 --> 08:55.750
Bow, you are basically
his woman.

08:55.750 --> 08:58.290
No, I'm -- Dre, stop it.
You hooked him up
with the Innocence Project.

08:58.290 --> 09:00.210
I didn't know they were
gonna do anything.

09:00.210 --> 09:01.670
Oh, you didn't think
the Innocence Project

09:01.670 --> 09:03.960
was gonna get somebody off
who was innocent?

09:03.960 --> 09:05.790
I thought
he was guilty.

09:05.790 --> 09:08.120
Well, he's not.
And he's out.

09:08.120 --> 09:10.460
And I'm gonna
help him.

09:10.460 --> 09:13.500
Siri, get me directions
to prison.

09:13.500 --> 09:15.290
Siri: Getting directions
to AmeriSuites.

09:15.290 --> 09:16.750
Told you.

09:16.750 --> 09:24.290
♪♪

09:24.290 --> 09:26.210
[ Sighs ]
I keep telling you,

09:26.210 --> 09:28.170
if we want to beat
the new twins,

09:28.170 --> 09:29.920
we need a chest bump
at the end.

09:29.920 --> 09:32.170
Say "chest bump"
one more time!

09:32.170 --> 09:33.750
Hey, guys,
can you keep it down?

09:33.750 --> 09:35.540
I'm juggling a lot
right now

09:35.540 --> 09:37.620
being the keeper
of the family secrets.

09:37.620 --> 09:39.330
Uh, what are you
talking about?

09:39.330 --> 09:41.420
Well, if I told you,
it wouldn't be a secret.

09:41.420 --> 09:44.460
Let's just say I learned
some pretty troubling
stuff about Grandma.

09:44.460 --> 09:46.290
About her going
to jail?
Oh, yeah.

09:46.290 --> 09:48.290
She stabbed that "B" Sheila
in the breadbasket.

09:48.290 --> 09:50.710
Ironically, it was
over cornbread, so...

09:50.710 --> 09:51.710
You knew?

09:51.710 --> 09:52.880
Of course we knew.

09:52.880 --> 09:54.500
We're part
of this family.

09:54.500 --> 09:56.750
Why am I the only one
who's been kept in the dark?

09:56.750 --> 09:58.000
Because you're soft.

09:58.000 --> 09:59.540
That's why
they haven't told you

09:59.540 --> 10:01.920
about any of our family's
ugly criminal history.

10:01.920 --> 10:03.750
What?
Dad went to mall jail

10:03.750 --> 10:06.380
for taking too many samples
at the fancy candy store.

10:06.380 --> 10:08.620
They found truffles
in his undies.

10:08.620 --> 10:11.250
And don't forget when
Pops pretended he fixed TVs.

10:11.250 --> 10:14.920
I'll get it back to you
in no time at all.

10:14.920 --> 10:16.040
[ Exhales ]

10:16.040 --> 10:18.380
Coco, start the van!

10:18.380 --> 10:19.420
[ Chuckles ]

10:19.420 --> 10:21.170
Oh, and don't forget
about Uncle Omar.

10:21.170 --> 10:23.080
He's in the hospital.
[ Scoffs ]

10:23.080 --> 10:24.830
Think about it,
Junior.

10:24.830 --> 10:27.120
Who goes to the hospital
for 10 to 15 years?

10:27.120 --> 10:28.290
Never heard of that.

10:28.290 --> 10:30.540
Every time I think
I'm closer to the truth,

10:30.540 --> 10:33.000
I'm punched in the face
with another lie.

10:33.000 --> 10:35.830
♪♪

10:35.830 --> 10:38.040
So, I was thinking,
at the end,

10:38.040 --> 10:39.750
we should
jump in the air

10:39.750 --> 10:42.790
and lightly touch the top part
of our bodies together.

10:42.790 --> 10:45.000
You know you're just describing
a chest bump, right?

10:45.000 --> 10:47.120
I just believe in it
so much.

10:47.120 --> 10:48.710
It's easy.
All you have to --

10:48.710 --> 10:50.040
Nope.

10:50.040 --> 10:51.500
Mnh-mnh.

10:51.500 --> 10:54.620
I really want to help Omar,
but Bow?

10:54.620 --> 10:55.670
She doesn't even want

10:55.670 --> 10:57.580
to let him crash on the couch
for a night.

10:57.580 --> 10:59.960
And I'm gonna have trouble
helping you with your problems

10:59.960 --> 11:02.000
until I see those
bathing-suit pictures.

11:02.000 --> 11:05.040
Are we talking
two-piece?

11:05.040 --> 11:06.120
You know what?
Don't worry about it.

11:06.120 --> 11:08.120
I'ma just
imagine something.

11:08.120 --> 11:10.540
Stevens: Look, I have to side
with Rainbow in this, Dre.

11:10.540 --> 11:14.210
You can't let
an ex-con stay with you.

11:14.210 --> 11:16.170
That's like letting
a Princeton man

11:16.170 --> 11:17.540
alone
with your daughter.

11:17.540 --> 11:19.000
[ Laughs ]

11:19.000 --> 11:20.460
Oh, come on.

11:20.460 --> 11:21.920
That would have killed
at the country club.

11:21.920 --> 11:23.040
You know what?
I'm gonna text them,

11:23.040 --> 11:23.960
'cause that was gold.

11:23.960 --> 11:26.170
Omar is not an ex-con.

11:26.170 --> 11:27.670
He's innocent.

11:27.670 --> 11:30.080
They're letting him out
because he didn't do it.

11:30.080 --> 11:31.960
And if he's black
and they let him out,

11:31.960 --> 11:33.500
he really must
not have done it.

11:33.500 --> 11:35.250
Well, just because
they found the guy innocent

11:35.250 --> 11:36.790
doesn't mean
that he didn't do it.

11:36.790 --> 11:38.380
It just means
they couldn't prove it.

11:38.380 --> 11:39.920
It's all about
what you can prove.

11:39.920 --> 11:41.380
Isn't that right,
Daddy?
Bup, bup, bup, bup.

11:41.380 --> 11:44.420
Stinker, hey, remember,
we signed the little contract?

11:44.420 --> 11:46.420
Yeah. So shh.
[ Chuckles ]

11:46.420 --> 11:49.210
So, I'm not supposed
to let Omar stay with me,

11:49.210 --> 11:50.920
even though
he is innocent?

11:50.920 --> 11:53.080
But you let Darrington
work here.

11:53.080 --> 11:55.290
Darrington has been
rehabilitated.

11:55.290 --> 11:58.040
Darrington has served
his debt to society,

11:58.040 --> 12:00.460
and Darrington deserves
a second chance.

12:00.460 --> 12:04.210
Omar served a debt
that wasn't even his.

12:04.210 --> 12:05.460
Can he come
work here?

12:05.460 --> 12:07.540
[ Laughs ]
Come on, Dre.

12:07.540 --> 12:08.750
We all know
that answer.

12:08.750 --> 12:10.580
This is ridiculous.

12:10.580 --> 12:12.750
The only thing
that Omar is guilty of

12:12.750 --> 12:13.960
is being in prison,

12:13.960 --> 12:16.210
and does that make him
damaged goods?

12:16.210 --> 12:18.210
I-Imagine how hard
it's gonna be

12:18.210 --> 12:20.120
for him to get his life back
when he gets out.

12:20.120 --> 12:24.540
He lost his house, his wife,
years of work experience.

12:24.540 --> 12:27.120
Yeah, life has marched on
without him.

12:27.120 --> 12:29.500
Bet he's never even
seen "New Girl."

12:29.500 --> 12:32.500
It's messed up, man.
The system is really broken.

12:32.500 --> 12:35.000
No, the system
is shattered.

12:35.000 --> 12:39.080
We put people in a machine
that's designed to break them,

12:39.080 --> 12:40.580
and then we turn
our backs on them

12:40.580 --> 12:42.040
when they come out
broken.

12:42.040 --> 12:43.790
I'm not gonna
do that to Omar.

12:43.790 --> 12:46.080
He's gonna stay with me
as long as it takes

12:46.080 --> 12:47.040
for him to get
back on his feet.

12:47.040 --> 12:48.290
That's wonderful, Dre.

12:48.290 --> 12:51.210
You have just let
a Princeton Tiger

12:51.210 --> 12:52.750
loose in your house.

12:52.750 --> 12:55.000
[ Chuckles ]

12:55.000 --> 12:56.540
Oh, this is wasted
on you two!

12:56.540 --> 12:58.830
You know what?
You know who would love this?

12:58.830 --> 12:59.620
Darrington.

12:59.620 --> 13:02.040
Darrington.

13:02.040 --> 13:04.620
Come here, you crazy,
little coke freak.

13:04.620 --> 13:09.620
♪♪

13:09.620 --> 13:11.000
Why are you
making up the couch?

13:11.000 --> 13:12.710
I got the hotel room.

13:12.710 --> 13:14.000
No, babe.

13:14.000 --> 13:15.460
Omar's gonna stay here,
all right?

13:15.460 --> 13:17.830
He -- He needs to be
surrounded by family.

13:17.830 --> 13:19.250
Uh, technically,

13:19.250 --> 13:20.710
he's not even family,
all right?

13:20.710 --> 13:22.290
He's your
old neighbor's son.

13:22.290 --> 13:23.920
And I've loved talking
on the phone with him,

13:23.920 --> 13:26.540
but I don't feel good

13:26.540 --> 13:29.330
about having a guy that's been
in prison for years

13:29.330 --> 13:30.540
stay on our couch.

13:30.540 --> 13:32.960
Oh, so now
he's just a "guy"?

13:32.960 --> 13:34.120
Dre, you know
what I mean.

13:34.120 --> 13:36.380
No, I -- I don't.
He's not just a guy.

13:36.380 --> 13:38.580
But being in prison
can be very rough.

13:38.580 --> 13:39.750
You have to go?

13:39.750 --> 13:41.620
What?
Why?

13:41.620 --> 13:42.670
Lockdown?

13:42.670 --> 13:45.210
You got a cellphone
smuggled in how?

13:45.210 --> 13:46.830
Solitary?

13:46.830 --> 13:48.380
Well, for how long?

13:48.380 --> 13:49.380
Are you okay?

13:49.380 --> 13:50.920
People come back,

13:50.920 --> 13:52.290
and it's like
they have PTSD.

13:52.290 --> 13:53.880
It's like they're coming home
from war.

13:53.880 --> 13:56.210
This is fascinating.

13:56.210 --> 13:58.000
Please -- Please, tell me
all about prison, Bow.

13:58.000 --> 13:59.540
Oh, my God, Dre.

13:59.540 --> 14:02.670
I know that things
happened to Omar

14:02.670 --> 14:05.420
that he didn't want
to tell me about.

14:05.420 --> 14:07.830
We have no idea
where his head is at.

14:07.830 --> 14:10.330
Well, I know Omar,

14:10.330 --> 14:12.330
and he didn't let
those things affect him.

14:12.330 --> 14:13.920
You don't know that,
Dre.

14:13.920 --> 14:16.790
Bow, we are his last line
of defense, all right?

14:16.790 --> 14:18.880
He deserves a chance
to start over.

14:18.880 --> 14:21.080
Of course he does.

14:21.080 --> 14:23.830
Just not in my house, Dre.
It's not safe.

14:23.830 --> 14:26.120
This isn't just
your house.

14:26.120 --> 14:27.670
Our house.

14:27.670 --> 14:29.330
Our family.

14:29.330 --> 14:32.170
He is not coming near
either of them.

14:32.170 --> 14:34.750
You don't just get to make
a decision like that, Bow.

14:34.750 --> 14:35.670
Yes, I do.

14:35.670 --> 14:37.000
And I just did.

14:42.750 --> 14:44.500
You tried
to keep it from me,

14:44.500 --> 14:46.000
but now I know
the truth.

14:46.000 --> 14:48.120
Uncle Omar's in jail?!

14:48.120 --> 14:49.620
He just got out.

14:49.620 --> 14:52.120
♪♪

14:52.120 --> 14:54.040
Even my secrets
have secrets.

14:58.330 --> 14:59.290
Grandma, I feel like
I'm the last one

14:59.290 --> 15:00.210
to know anything
around here.

15:00.210 --> 15:02.540
You all think I'm soft,
but I'm not.

15:02.540 --> 15:04.880
My voice hasn't cracked
in three months.

15:04.880 --> 15:07.380
So you think you're ready
for the truth, huh?

15:07.380 --> 15:09.460
Yes.
I want to know it all.

15:09.460 --> 15:10.620
Okay.

15:10.620 --> 15:15.620
So, you know, every beach
is not a nude beach.

15:15.620 --> 15:18.040
So, as we lay there
together,

15:18.040 --> 15:20.790
Stevie Wonder said
he could see.

15:20.790 --> 15:23.080
So, apparently, you're not
allowed to punch

15:23.080 --> 15:24.790
a policeman's horse,
either.

15:24.790 --> 15:28.330
So then I put my gun
in Phil Spector's mouth.

15:28.330 --> 15:30.670
So they look like
little balloons,

15:30.670 --> 15:33.210
and what I had to do
was swallow them whole.

15:33.210 --> 15:35.960
[ Chuckles ] And just pray
they didn't burst inside me.

15:35.960 --> 15:37.540
[ Chuckles ] Or else
it would have been

15:37.540 --> 15:38.750
night-night, Grandma.

15:38.750 --> 15:40.120
[ Chuckles ]

15:40.120 --> 15:42.000
So that was the '80s.

15:42.000 --> 15:43.500
You know...

15:43.500 --> 15:44.580
[ Voice cracks ]
We're good.

15:44.580 --> 15:45.620
Okay.

15:45.620 --> 15:46.830
Thanks for the honesty.

15:46.830 --> 15:48.920
Anytime, baby.

15:48.920 --> 15:50.540
♪♪

15:50.540 --> 15:51.710
[ Cans clatter ]

15:51.710 --> 15:53.540
Dre, if you're trying
to make me feel bad,

15:53.540 --> 15:55.960
can you do it without
waking the baby up?

15:55.960 --> 15:57.710
You should feel bad.

15:57.710 --> 15:59.670
You're a terrible person.
That's nice.

15:59.670 --> 16:02.210
Since you made it clear
that Omar isn't welcome here,

16:02.210 --> 16:05.000
I am going out
to meet him,

16:05.000 --> 16:06.250
and I'm bringing him
a few things.

16:06.250 --> 16:09.880
Your "welcome to freedom" move
is used hot sauce?

16:09.880 --> 16:12.380
The man completely missed
the rise of sriracha.

16:12.380 --> 16:14.080
Okay, Dre.
It's your call,

16:14.080 --> 16:16.000
but I would have started
with a new phone.

16:16.000 --> 16:17.290
Look,
this isn't funny, Bow.

16:17.290 --> 16:19.880
When I think about
where Omar is right now,

16:19.880 --> 16:21.380
I can only go
to bad places.

16:21.380 --> 16:24.380
I think about solitary,
gangs,

16:24.380 --> 16:25.670
and not to mention
what what happened

16:25.670 --> 16:26.750
with Kalief Browder.

16:26.750 --> 16:27.710
Oh, my God.

16:27.710 --> 16:28.790
The kid was innocent,

16:28.790 --> 16:30.330
and he was thrown in jail
for years

16:30.330 --> 16:32.420
for a crime
he didn't commit.

16:32.420 --> 16:34.580
They tortured him
in there.
I know.

16:34.580 --> 16:36.710
And when he got out,
he couldn't cope.

16:36.710 --> 16:38.420
I know.
I know.

16:38.420 --> 16:40.920
So he killed himself.

16:40.920 --> 16:42.580
[ Sighs ]

16:42.580 --> 16:45.210
That could happen to Omar.

16:45.210 --> 16:47.170
But, Dre, you can't
think like that.

16:47.170 --> 16:49.330
How else should I
be thinking, Bow?

16:49.330 --> 16:51.960
Right now, Omar's being
dropped off downtown

16:51.960 --> 16:55.420
with $40 in his pocket
and no place to go.

16:55.420 --> 16:59.420
So I'm gonna be there
for him.

16:59.420 --> 17:00.920
With some Popchips.

17:02.710 --> 17:04.420
♪♪

17:04.420 --> 17:05.290
Girl: Hey!

17:05.290 --> 17:06.210
Cool!

17:06.210 --> 17:07.750
♪ Ahhh ♪

17:07.750 --> 17:08.920
♪ Begin, begin ♪

17:08.920 --> 17:11.380
♪ Go, go, go, go ♪

17:11.380 --> 17:12.580
♪ Ahhh ♪

17:12.580 --> 17:13.580
♪ Begin, begin ♪

17:13.580 --> 17:16.670
♪♪

17:16.670 --> 17:17.670
♪ Break ♪

17:17.670 --> 17:18.750
[ Indistinct chattering ]

17:18.750 --> 17:19.790
Girl #2: New hats!

17:19.790 --> 17:22.330
Hey, look,
the twins got new hats!

17:22.330 --> 17:23.830
OMG.

17:23.830 --> 17:24.960
You guys.

17:24.960 --> 17:26.250
[ Laughing ]
They're cute!

17:26.250 --> 17:27.540
[ Students "Aww" ]
Oh, Dylan.

17:27.540 --> 17:28.880
Wrong again.

17:28.880 --> 17:30.380
[ Laughter ]

17:30.380 --> 17:31.290
[ Laughs ]

17:31.290 --> 17:32.830
Boy:
Those hats are dope.

17:32.830 --> 17:35.080
Why didn't we think
of hats?

17:35.080 --> 17:36.290
Because we're
playing checkers,

17:36.290 --> 17:38.120
and they're
playing chess.

17:38.120 --> 17:42.670
♪♪

17:42.670 --> 17:43.460
[ Scoffs ]

17:46.330 --> 17:48.580
[ Doorbells jingle ]

17:48.580 --> 17:54.250
♪♪

17:54.250 --> 17:55.460
What are you doing here?

17:55.460 --> 17:56.880
Move over.

17:59.170 --> 18:02.580
[ Sighs ]

18:02.580 --> 18:04.920
For once, you were being
the better person,

18:04.920 --> 18:06.380
and I am not comfortable
with that.

18:09.540 --> 18:10.790
This needs
green sauce.

18:13.420 --> 18:14.120
Ah.

18:15.960 --> 18:17.620
I don't feel good
about how I reacted

18:17.620 --> 18:20.420
to all this stuff
with Omar.

18:20.420 --> 18:22.420
I mean, if it were
just the two of us,

18:22.420 --> 18:25.500
maybe it would be different,
but we have children.

18:25.500 --> 18:28.000
You don't think
I've thought about this?

18:28.000 --> 18:29.290
I love
most of our kids.

18:29.290 --> 18:31.420
Dre, stop it.
Okay.

18:31.420 --> 18:32.880
Oh, that -- that's just
for the table.

18:32.880 --> 18:33.920
What?

18:35.380 --> 18:36.960
What?

18:36.960 --> 18:39.080
Dre, how many people
are you ordering for?

18:39.080 --> 18:41.420
The man hasn't eaten
a delicious meal

18:41.420 --> 18:42.750
in who knows how long.

18:42.750 --> 18:43.880
Okay.

18:43.880 --> 18:44.960
And when he does
get here,

18:44.960 --> 18:46.500
I'm still gonna order
whatever he wants.

18:47.960 --> 18:50.120
I'm not gonna lie.

18:50.120 --> 18:52.500
I don't know if I'm doing
the right thing.

18:52.500 --> 18:55.210
[ Doorbells jingle ]
I don't know.

18:55.210 --> 18:58.170
I'm nervous about who's
gonna walk through that door.

18:58.170 --> 19:00.460
But I do know

19:00.460 --> 19:03.080
that I'm supposed
to be right here.

19:03.080 --> 19:04.420
Waiter:
Here's your bacon.
Oh, oh, I'll take that.

19:04.420 --> 19:05.250
Okay. Wow.

19:05.250 --> 19:06.040
And your fruit.

19:06.040 --> 19:07.380
Okay. Really?

19:07.380 --> 19:09.790
Hey, um, do you think
he's Muslim now?

19:09.790 --> 19:10.710
Uh...

19:10.710 --> 19:12.120
You know what?

19:12.120 --> 19:13.420
I'll just eat
the bacon.

19:13.420 --> 19:15.170
Is there anything
that's gonna stop you

19:15.170 --> 19:16.210
from eating
the bacon, Dre?

19:16.210 --> 19:17.710
Mm-hmm.
More bacon.

19:17.710 --> 19:18.830
[ Laughs ]

19:18.830 --> 19:19.750
[ Doorbells jingle ]

19:19.750 --> 19:20.960
♪♪

19:24.880 --> 19:26.080
Hey. Have you seen my phone?

19:26.080 --> 19:27.170
Has anyone seen
my CD headphones?

19:27.170 --> 19:29.830
Has anyone seen
my $5 million?

19:29.830 --> 19:31.040
Guys, I think
we've been robbed.

19:31.040 --> 19:32.000
Oh, my God,

19:32.000 --> 19:33.000
and on the same day

19:33.000 --> 19:34.460
that Darrington leaves

19:34.460 --> 19:36.920
for his trip to French Guyana.

19:36.920 --> 19:38.880
Dre, do you, uh --

19:38.880 --> 19:41.000
Do you have anything
you want to tell us?

19:41.000 --> 19:42.290
Yeah, Dre.
Do you?

19:42.290 --> 19:44.000
Yeah.

19:44.000 --> 19:46.040
Darrington robbed you.

19:46.040 --> 19:48.250
Right!

19:48.250 --> 19:49.710
Right! Definitely!

19:49.710 --> 19:51.290
Makes logical sense.

19:51.290 --> 19:52.670
Mm.

19:52.670 --> 19:53.750
Still, Dre,
I may have to go

19:53.750 --> 19:54.920
through your pockets.

19:54.920 --> 20:00.120
♪♪
